gonna be able to have children?

1:04:56.204 --> 1:04:57.270
I'm afraid so.

1:04:57.272 --> 1:04:58.307
Hey. It's okay.

1:05:00.810 --> 1:05:02.712
No, no, it's not.

1:05:03.846 --> 1:05:05.213
I love kids.

1:05:06.248 --> 1:05:08.582
You're so good
with kids.

1:05:08.584 --> 1:05:11.251
Melissa,
it's my professional opinion

1:05:11.253 --> 1:05:13.288
that this is
absolutely necessary,

1:05:14.456 --> 1:05:16.156
given your condition

1:05:16.158 --> 1:05:17.257
and what we're seeing
on the tests.

1:05:17.259 --> 1:05:19.860
Well, then run more tests,
please. Just run more tests.

1:05:19.862 --> 1:05:21.129
We've run them all.

1:05:22.464 --> 1:05:24.099
And they're very conclusive.

1:05:25.300 --> 1:05:26.366
Mmm.

1:05:33.676 --> 1:05:35.210
Want me
to make you something?

1:05:36.511 --> 1:05:37.814
No, I got it.

1:05:39.716 --> 1:05:41.516
- Here. Let me do it.
- No, no. It's okay.

1:05:42.484 --> 1:05:44.119
I need a second.

1:06:24.694 --> 1:06:25.695
Oh!

1:06:32.367 --> 1:06:34.169
Oh, no. Oh, God.

1:06:37.339 --> 1:06:38.505
Hey.

1:06:38.507 --> 1:06:40.810
No, no. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

1:06:42.611 --> 1:06:45.614
Okay, okay.
I just can't...

1:06:57.325 --> 1:06:58.693
<i>Welcome back to The Fish,</i>

1:06:58.695 --> 1:06:59.694
<i>Los Angeles,</i>

1:06:59.696 --> 1:07:00.828
<i>and we have
a great young artist</i>

1:07:00.830 --> 1:07:02.063
<i>in the studio with us today,
Jeremy Camp.</i>

1:07:02.065 --> 1:07:04.899
<i>Yes. And Jeremy's
gonna do some songs</i>

1:07:04.901 --> 1:07:06.499
<i>live for us in just a minute.</i>

1:07:06.501 --> 1:07:07.667
<i>But first, Jeremy,</i>

1:07:07.669 --> 1:07:10.437
<i>you have some pretty big news
you wanted to share with us?</i>

1:07:10.439 --> 1:07:11.538
<i>I do, yeah.</i>

1:07:11.540 --> 1:07:13.506
First off, thank you so much
for having me.

1:07:13.508 --> 1:07:17.477
Um, for everyone listening,
my fiancee's name is Melissa.

1:07:17.479 --> 1:07:18.846
Uh,

1:07:18.848 --> 1:07:21.281
she has a huge surgery
coming up this week,

1:07:21.283 --> 1:07:22.950
and it's really serious.

1:07:22.952 --> 1:07:25.720
And basically,
she needs a miracle.

1:07:25.722 --> 1:07:28.354
So I just wanted to
ask everyone listening,

1:07:28.356 --> 1:07:31.391
if you could just stop
what you're doing and pray.

1:07:31.393 --> 1:07:33.928
<i>I'll do the playing.
You guys do the praying.</i>

1:07:33.930 --> 1:07:35.562
<i>Thank you.</i>

1:08:20.877 --> 1:08:22.410
- Hey, buddy.
- Hey.

1:08:22.945 --> 1:08:24.044
I, uh...

1:08:24.046 --> 1:08:25.748
I stopped by
the radio station,

1:08:27.016 --> 1:08:29.083
and it's like
the whole city's praying.

1:08:29.085 --> 1:08:31.018
Dude, these letters are
pouring in from everywhere.

1:08:31.020 --> 1:08:32.652
No way.

1:08:32.654 --> 1:08:34.891
I thought
you'd want to have them.

1:08:35.958 --> 1:08:37.357
Hang in there.

1:08:37.359 --> 1:08:38.527
Thanks, man.

1:09:00.783 --> 1:09:02.051
Can I sit with you?

1:09:03.418 --> 1:09:04.419
Yeah.

1:09:16.098 --> 1:09:18.567
It's so weird
seeing her here.

1:09:19.936 --> 1:09:21.636
She's always been
the strong one.

1:09:24.740 --> 1:09:26.042
Yeah.

1:09:28.044 --> 1:09:30.913
I'm really glad that
in the midst of all of this,

1:09:32.414 --> 1:09:33.716
someone is choosing her,

1:09:35.117 --> 1:09:36.752
someone really special.

1:09:38.420 --> 1:09:41.521
Thank you for giving her
a chance...

1:09:41.523 --> 1:09:42.524
Jeremy!

1:09:42.792 --> 1:09:43.793
Jeremy!

1:09:47.196 --> 1:09:48.461
Yeah.

1:10:02.577 --> 1:10:03.744
Mmm.

1:10:10.152 --> 1:10:11.153
Hey.

1:10:12.889 --> 1:10:13.890
Jeremy.

1:10:21.463 --> 1:10:23.063
Your cancer,

1:10:23.065 --> 1:10:25.065
it's gone.

1:10:25.067 --> 1:10:27.069
They didn't go through
with the surgery.

1:10:28.704 --> 1:10:30.072
You're cancer-free.

1:10:31.673 --> 1:10:34.176
And that is the story you're
gonna tell our kids one day.

1:10:41.183 --> 1:10:42.683
You know what you are?

1:10:42.685 --> 1:10:44.617
<i>If
anyone here has ever wondered</i>

1:10:44.619 --> 1:10:45.788
<i>if miracles still happen,</i>

1:10:47.056 --> 1:10:48.991
<i>or if God still heals,</i>

1:10:51.093 --> 1:10:52.226
<i>then I wanna introduce you</i>

1:10:52.228 --> 1:10:54.196
<i>to the most beautiful girl
in this room.</i>

1:11:22.657 --> 1:11:23.993
You're a miracle.

1:11:25.660 --> 1:11:26.829
That's what you are.

1:11:38.975 --> 1:11:40.209
<i>It's unbelievable.</i>

1:11:41.143 --> 1:11:44.111
<i>I spoke to the doctor myself.</i>

1:11:44.113 --> 1:11:46.680
<i>There is literally
no medical explanation,</i>

1:11:46.682 --> 1:11:48.614
none whatsoever.

1:11:48.616 --> 1:11:49.683
That is awesome.

1:11:49.685 --> 1:11:50.951
For everyone listening
out there,

1:11:50.953 --> 1:11:52.686
<i>on positive,
encouraging K-LOVE,</i>

1:11:52.688 --> 1:11:54.888
<i>she's 100% cancer-free.</i>

1:11:54.890 --> 1:11:56.622
<i>Amen. Yes, she is.</i>

1:12:40.736 --> 1:12:42.836
I will love you,

1:12:42.838 --> 1:12:44.772
cherish you,

1:12:44.774 --> 1:12:45.841
honor you,

1:12:46.942 --> 1:12:49.309
every moment of every day

1:12:49.311 --> 1:12:50.813
without hesitation

1:12:51.613 --> 1:12:52.782
and never looking back.

1:12:53.983 --> 1:12:56.250
I'll encourage you,

1:12:56.252 --> 1:12:57.720
lift you up,

1:12:58.788 --> 1:13:00.788
I'll be your muse

1:13:00.790 --> 1:13:03.025
and your anchor.

1:13:04.760 --> 1:13:06.628
I'll be the love of your life

1:13:07.730 --> 1:13:10.199
and your biggest fan.

1:13:11.367 --> 1:13:13.302
Until death do we part.

1:13:14.370 --> 1:13:16.739
Nope, past that.

1:13:18.007 --> 1:13:19.742
I will love you past that.

1:13:22.378 --> 1:13:25.214
Son, you may
kiss the bride.

1:13:31.153 --> 1:13:32.652
Ladies and gentlemen,

1:13:32.654 --> 1:13:35.022
- Mr. and Mrs. Jeremy Camp.
- Aw.

1:14:37.853 --> 1:14:39.753
Through the storm
and out the other side.

1:14:39.755 --> 1:14:40.756
Can you believe it?

1:14:41.423 --> 1:14:42.791
Mmm-mmm.

1:14:45.995 --> 1:14:48.898
Thank you,
Jeremy Camp.

1:14:50.266 --> 1:14:53.500
I think I would have died
without you.

1:14:53.502 --> 1:14:55.738
I would have been lost
and alone at sea.

1:14:58.374 --> 1:15:00.843
God sent you to save me.

1:15:04.947 --> 1:15:07.781
Melissa Camp.

1:15:07.783 --> 1:15:10.217
I like
the sound of that.

1:15:10.219 --> 1:15:11.518
- <i>Ready?</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

1:15:11.520 --> 1:15:14.356
- Okay. One, two, three.
- ...two, three.

1:15:22.131 --> 1:15:22.932
What did you wish for?

1:15:24.233 --> 1:15:25.801
I wrote down
some names...

1:15:26.902 --> 1:15:29.136
Names I've been dreaming of.

1:15:29.138 --> 1:15:31.006
- Family?
- Mmm-hmm.

1:15:35.277 --> 1:15:38.178
I've got
a surprise for you tomorrow.

1:15:38.180 --> 1:15:39.348
- Really?
- Mmm-hmm.

1:16:16.085 --> 1:16:17.150
Phew.

1:16:17.152 --> 1:16:19.154
That's, uh,
so strange.

1:16:19.989 --> 1:16:21.088
What?

1:16:21.090 --> 1:16:23.357
Oh, uh...
I don't know.

1:16:23.359 --> 1:16:24.958
You've never
been sailing

1:16:24.960 --> 1:16:26.295
and I'm the one
who gets sick.

1:16:37.973 --> 1:16:40.841
<i>♪ Will I believe You</i>

1:16:40.843 --> 1:16:43.078
<i>♪ When You say</i>

1:16:45.281 --> 1:16:51.053
<i>♪ That Your hand will guide me
In every way</i>

1:17:00.329 --> 1:17:03.063
<i>♪ Walk by me</i>

1:17:12.608 --> 1:17:16.145
Jeremy. Hey. Hey.

1:17:21.317 --> 1:17:23.085
Something's wrong.

1:17:24.953 --> 1:17:28.257
Something is really wrong.

1:17:39.902 --> 1:17:40.969
Hey.

1:17:41.637 --> 1:17:42.838
How does it feel?

1:17:54.383 --> 1:17:56.416
- Jeremy.
- Hey. Wanna come in?

1:17:56.418 --> 1:17:58.587
No. Actually,
let's talk out here.

1:18:05.494 --> 1:18:07.060
So, what's going on?

1:18:07.062 --> 1:18:09.998
She's having a little
pain, feeling bloated.

1:18:11.567 --> 1:18:14.503
Liss, hey.
I'm sure it's fine.

1:18:15.337 --> 1:18:16.670
The cancer's come back.

1:18:16.672 --> 1:18:18.874
It's spreading rapidly.
It's all over her body.

1:18:25.080 --> 1:18:27.547
Okay. What does that mean?

1:18:27.549 --> 1:18:29.583
That means we have
to have another surgery?

1:18:29.585 --> 1:18:32.619
No. No more surgeries.

1:18:32.621 --> 1:18:33.622
What? Chemo then?

1:18:35.991 --> 1:18:38.026
No. We're stopping
treatments.

1:18:39.395 --> 1:18:41.461
There's nothing else
we can do.

1:18:41.463 --> 1:18:42.529
I'm afraid to say

1:18:42.531 --> 1:18:44.133
she only has
a few weeks,

1:18:45.134 --> 1:18:46.402
a couple months
at the most.

1:18:48.070 --> 1:18:49.405
I'm so sorry, Jeremy.

1:19:38.020 --> 1:19:39.021
I'll be right back.

1:20:43.252 --> 1:20:44.719
Okay.

1:20:44.721 --> 1:20:46.188
This should help
with the pain.

1:20:51.326 --> 1:20:52.327
Squirt.

1:20:54.263 --> 1:20:55.531
Clamp.

1:20:57.099 --> 1:20:58.100
Swab.

1:21:11.647 --> 1:21:12.648
Okay.

1:21:15.785 --> 1:21:16.786
We got this.

1:21:23.191 --> 1:21:24.359
We got this.

1:21:30.465 --> 1:21:33.734
Is there a concert
I didn't know about?

1:21:33.736 --> 1:21:36.338
Not a great turnout,
Jeremy Camp.

1:21:38.407 --> 1:21:40.108
No. I just wanted you
to see it.

1:21:43.378 --> 1:21:44.379
See what?

1:21:46.281 --> 1:21:47.449
Where it happened for me.

1:21:49.551 --> 1:21:50.787
This is where
I was standing.

1:21:52.889 --> 1:21:54.556
Right here,

1:21:55.758 --> 1:21:57.457
when I fell in love with you.

1:21:59.796 --> 1:22:01.597
Come on. "Fell in love?"

1:22:02.765 --> 1:22:04.499
- On the first night?
- Yeah.

1:22:07.937 --> 1:22:09.806
You were sitting
right there.

1:22:12.909 --> 1:22:17.880
The girl who sat there
seems so far away now.

1:22:20.817 --> 1:22:22.819
I feel like
a shadow of her.

1:22:26.288 --> 1:22:27.623
On our first date,

1:22:29.458 --> 1:22:30.760
you said,

1:22:32.829 --> 1:22:33.928
"Some stars

1:22:33.930 --> 1:22:35.597
"shine brighter than others."

1:22:37.900 --> 1:22:40.502
You know the stars
that shine the brightest?

1:22:44.941 --> 1:22:47.175
The ones
with the shortest life.

1:22:49.444 --> 1:22:50.880
And when they die,

1:22:52.749 --> 1:22:56.650
they explode
in a supernova.

1:22:56.652 --> 1:22:57.653
It's...

1:22:58.654 --> 1:23:00.522
It's the most
beautiful thing.

1:23:02.357 --> 1:23:05.928
Color and light
all mixed together,

1:23:08.765 --> 1:23:09.932
God's painting.

1:23:12.902 --> 1:23:14.969
The death
of a single star

1:23:14.971 --> 1:23:17.570
outshines everything
else in the galaxy.

1:23:17.572 --> 1:23:18.573
Melissa.

1:23:23.913 --> 1:23:25.980
What if I'm not
supposed to be healed?

1:23:25.982 --> 1:23:28.350
No, don't. Don't.

1:23:29.518 --> 1:23:30.383
Don't say that.

1:23:30.385 --> 1:23:32.487
I want you to
promise me something.

1:23:35.758 --> 1:23:37.490
I want you
to find someone else.

1:23:37.492 --> 1:23:38.895
Don't. Don't.

1:23:50.472 --> 1:23:51.974
You're going to be healed.

1:23:54.811 --> 1:23:55.910
I promise you that.

1:23:55.912 --> 1:23:56.913
Jeremy.

1:23:59.281 --> 1:24:00.615
Would you just stop?

1:24:03.820 --> 1:24:06.956
Stop making promises
that aren't yours to make.

1:24:37.954 --> 1:24:39.086
Jeez. Did I forget the dose?

1:24:39.088 --> 1:24:41.554
It hurts. It hurts.

1:24:41.556 --> 1:24:42.957
So bad.

1:24:42.959 --> 1:24:44.657
- I'm okay. I'm okay.
- Melissa. No. You're not okay.

1:24:44.659 --> 1:24:45.726
- Come on.
- No. I'm okay.

1:24:45.728 --> 1:24:47.362
We're going to the hospital.
Come on.

1:24:49.431 --> 1:24:51.968
Help! Somebody help!

1:24:52.835 --> 1:24:54.068
Somebody help!

1:24:54.070 --> 1:24:56.704
Nurse, we're gonna
need a wheelchair!

1:25:30.840 --> 1:25:32.541
When's the
last time you slept?

1:25:39.015 --> 1:25:41.081
Go home. Get some rest.
Go shower.

1:25:41.083 --> 1:25:43.583
- We got this.
- I can't.

1:25:43.585 --> 1:25:44.854
Just get a few hours.

1:25:46.555 --> 1:25:47.855
Come on. Go home.

1:25:50.625 --> 1:25:51.961
She is my home.

1:26:13.716 --> 1:26:14.717
Hey.

1:26:16.185 --> 1:26:17.385
Hey.

1:26:28.663 --> 1:26:29.999
Did you finish the song,

1:26:32.001 --> 1:26:34.003
the one from our honeymoon?

1:26:36.839 --> 1:26:38.406
Yeah.

1:26:40.142 --> 1:26:42.044
Will you please
play it for me?

1:27:21.650 --> 1:27:26.989
<i>♪ Would you believe me
When I say</i>

1:27:28.523 --> 1:27:32.929
<i>♪ That Your hand
Will guide every way</i>

1:27:35.064 --> 1:27:41.037
<i>♪ Every moment, every day</i>

1:27:43.940 --> 1:27:48.811
<i>♪ Well, I will walk by faith</i>

1:27:50.947 --> 1:27:54.884
<i>♪ Even when I don't see</i>

1:27:57.687 --> 1:28:02.524
<i>♪ Even a broken road</i>

1:28:03.960 --> 1:28:08.030
<i>♪ Prepares Your will for me</i>

1:28:18.007 --> 1:28:23.578
<i>♪ Well, I will walk by faith</i>

1:28:26.983 --> 1:28:30.820
<i>♪ Even when I don't see</i>

1:28:35.191 --> 1:28:39.661
<i>♪ Even when I don't see</i>

1:28:55.211 --> 1:28:59.148
That was so beautiful.

1:29:24.373 --> 1:29:25.573
Are you okay?

1:29:31.947 --> 1:29:32.948
You okay?

1:29:35.284 --> 1:29:36.285
It's God.

1:29:38.087 --> 1:29:39.353
- It's God.
- What do you mean?

1:29:39.355 --> 1:29:41.221
I'm healed.

1:29:41.223 --> 1:29:43.323
It doesn't hurt anymore.
I can't feel it.

1:29:43.325 --> 1:29:44.725
You were right.

1:29:44.727 --> 1:29:46.326
I'm telling you,
I'm healed.

1:29:46.328 --> 1:29:47.361
I think I'm okay.
I think I'm okay.

1:29:47.363 --> 1:29:48.996
Babe, lie down, lie down.
I'll get the doctor.

1:29:48.998 --> 1:29:50.232
You have to believe me.

1:29:51.700 --> 1:29:52.768
Just believe me.

1:29:54.236 --> 1:29:55.271
I'm okay.

1:29:56.671 --> 1:29:59.239
Okay. I'm gonna
get the doctor.

1:29:59.241 --> 1:30:01.408
Excuse me, can I get
a doctor for my wife?

1:30:01.410 --> 1:30:03.243
Okay. Slow down.
What's the issue?

1:30:03.245 --> 1:30:06.680
Dr. Furst,
Melissa's awake.

1:30:07.783 --> 1:30:10.019
Someone help! Someone help!

1:30:20.296 --> 1:30:21.629
I love you.

1:30:34.410 --> 1:30:35.945
She's with Jesus.

1:30:42.184 --> 1:30:43.285
No.

1:30:50.426 --> 1:30:52.795
I didn't get to say goodbye.

1:31:05.474 --> 1:31:07.074
I'm Tom Camp.

1:31:07.076 --> 1:31:08.976
I'm looking for my son,
Jeremy.

1:31:08.978 --> 1:31:10.212
Mr. Camp.

1:31:11.247 --> 1:31:12.880
He's still in the room.

1:32:47.243 --> 1:32:49.142
Get some sleep.

1:32:49.144 --> 1:32:50.410
See you in the morning.

1:32:50.412 --> 1:32:53.814
Mom and I will have breakfast
ready for you when you get up.

1:32:53.816 --> 1:32:54.984
Dad?

1:32:58.988 --> 1:33:00.089
Can I ask you a question?

1:33:02.591 --> 1:33:03.859
Anything.

1:33:11.267 --> 1:33:13.969
I remember I prayed
and prayed in this room

1:33:16.305 --> 1:33:18.007
for Josh to be
born healthy.

1:33:21.076 --> 1:33:22.511
It didn't happen.

1:33:24.947 --> 1:33:27.116
And you prayed for so long
for your ministry.

1:33:30.486 --> 1:33:31.487
Still nothing.

1:33:33.555 --> 1:33:35.924
Dad, I begged God
to heal Melissa.

1:33:41.630 --> 1:33:43.332
What am I supposed
to do with that?

1:33:49.938 --> 1:33:53.573
Are you asking
if Josh's disabilities

1:33:53.575 --> 1:33:54.810
were disappointing?

1:33:59.048 --> 1:34:00.382
Yes, they are.

1:34:04.086 --> 1:34:06.586
Did I have big dreams
that didn't come true?

1:34:06.588 --> 1:34:07.589
Sure.

1:34:10.959 --> 1:34:14.129
Do I understand why Melissa
isn't here anymore?

1:34:17.299 --> 1:34:19.468
No, son, I don't.

1:34:22.905 --> 1:34:23.906
I'm sorry.

1:34:26.975 --> 1:34:28.844
But I know
my life is full.

1:34:32.348 --> 1:34:34.014
I feel rich,

1:34:34.016 --> 1:34:35.451
and I'm proud
of this family.

1:34:40.322 --> 1:34:41.521
Honestly, at the time,

1:34:41.523 --> 1:34:44.091
I didn't agree
with what you did.

1:34:44.093 --> 1:34:45.327
I didn't understand it.

1:34:48.230 --> 1:34:51.033
You chose willingly to walk
into the fire with her.

1:34:52.634 --> 1:34:55.237
Right beside her,
all the way to the end.

1:34:59.608 --> 1:35:01.241
But then,

1:35:01.243 --> 1:35:05.114
that's exactly what I would do
for your mom and you boys.

1:35:08.183 --> 1:35:09.518
That's what love is.

1:35:15.124 --> 1:35:17.292
And I got to watch
my son do that.

1:35:19.696 --> 1:35:20.896
For his wife.

1:35:22.598 --> 1:35:23.532
That was a privilege.

1:35:27.603 --> 1:35:30.272
I don't know the answers
to your questions.

1:35:34.176 --> 1:35:35.377
But I do know this,

1:35:37.279 --> 1:35:38.645
that my life is not full

1:35:38.647 --> 1:35:41.049
in spite of
the disappointments.

1:35:45.187 --> 1:35:46.689
It's full because of them.

1:35:53.128 --> 1:35:54.263
I'm proud of you.

1:35:56.999 --> 1:35:58.066
I love you, Dad.

1:36:27.262 --> 1:36:28.263
<i>Jeremy.</i>

1:36:30.265 --> 1:36:32.098
<i>I'm healed.</i>

1:36:32.100 --> 1:36:34.100
<i>I think I'm healed. It's God.</i>

1:36:34.102 --> 1:36:36.403
You know the stars
that shine the brightest?

1:36:36.405 --> 1:36:38.038
<i>The ones
with the shortest life.</i>

1:36:38.040 --> 1:36:39.172
You're going to be healed.

1:36:39.174 --> 1:36:40.607
<i>I need a doctor!</i>

1:36:40.609 --> 1:36:42.108
<i>I promise you.</i>

1:36:42.110 --> 1:36:43.477
<i>It doesn't hurt anymore.</i>

1:36:43.479 --> 1:36:44.511
<i>I can't feel it.</i>

1:36:44.513 --> 1:36:47.080
<i>You were right.
You have to believe...</i>

1:37:04.633 --> 1:37:06.068
Why did You do this?

1:38:28.818 --> 1:38:29.819
<i>Jeremy.</i>

1:38:31.888 --> 1:38:34.922
<i>I know
you'll find this someday.</i>

1:38:34.924 --> 1:38:39.694
<i>See? I'm finally letting you
read my journal.</i>

1:38:39.696 --> 1:38:43.432
<i>And I've thought a lot about
the day I realized I loved you.</i>

1:38:44.701 --> 1:38:45.702
<i>Remember?</i>

1:38:52.875 --> 1:38:58.211
<i>I just watched you there,
awestruck by your gift.</i>

1:38:58.213 --> 1:39:01.383
<i>Knowing God would use it
someday to touch the world.</i>

1:39:02.651 --> 1:39:04.887
<i>I felt that day
the same way I do now.</i>

1:39:08.825 --> 1:39:11.293
<i>You're asleep on my shoulder
right now.</i>

1:39:12.661 --> 1:39:13.794
<i>I guess one of the benefits</i>

1:39:13.796 --> 1:39:16.164
<i>of the pain is that
it's hard to sleep.</i>

1:39:17.432 --> 1:39:21.368
<i>Which means I have
a lot of time to think.</i>

1:39:21.370 --> 1:39:23.570
<i>And I've thought a lot
about the stories</i>

1:39:23.572 --> 1:39:26.341
<i>you love to tell
at your concerts.</i>

1:39:27.409 --> 1:39:28.811
<i>You're so good at it.</i>

1:39:30.212 --> 1:39:31.446
<i>Ancient stories,</i>

1:39:32.314 --> 1:39:34.249
<i>still relevant and true.</i>

1:39:35.718 --> 1:39:38.788
<i>In one story,
God grants healing.</i>

1:39:39.756 --> 1:39:42.489
<i>Miracles do happen.</i>

1:39:42.491 --> 1:39:46.428
<i>Yet to another, His call
is to suffer, and even die.</i>

1:39:48.731 --> 1:39:50.532
<i>And I realized something,</i>

1:39:52.601 --> 1:39:55.602
<i>they both have value.</i>

1:39:55.604 --> 1:39:58.906
<i>Because each is a chapter
in a bigger story.</i>

1:39:58.908 --> 1:40:03.576
<i>Each is the stroke of a brush
on His beautiful canvas.</i>

1:40:03.578 --> 1:40:09.418
<i>Each is the light of one star
helping to form a galaxy.</i>

1:40:11.921 --> 1:40:13.821
<i>And I think I'm one of
those lucky people</i>

1:40:13.823 --> 1:40:15.624
<i>meant to experience both.</i>

1:40:17.626 --> 1:40:19.960
<i>I had my miracle.</i>

1:40:19.962 --> 1:40:22.699
<i>It led to the perfect day
with you.</i>

1:40:23.331 --> 1:40:25.665
<i>It was enough.</i>

1:40:25.667 --> 1:40:29.737
<i>I've learned that suffering
doesn't destroy faith,</i>

1:40:29.739 --> 1:40:30.907
<i>it refines it.</i>

1:40:32.507 --> 1:40:34.875
<i>And God is worth trusting.</i>

1:40:34.877 --> 1:40:37.212
<i>Even when we can't see.</i>

1:40:38.547 --> 1:40:40.480
<i>I'm safe in His arms</i>

1:40:40.482 --> 1:40:42.683
<i>going bravely into the light
with a peace</i>

1:40:42.685 --> 1:40:45.287
<i>that I can't understand.</i>

1:41:01.070 --> 1:41:03.638
<i>So, do one thing
for me, Jeremy Camp,</i>

1:41:04.473 --> 1:41:06.306
<i>for my sake.</i>

1:41:06.308 --> 1:41:09.812
<i>For the sake of your gift
and everyone meant to hear it.</i>

1:41:13.448 --> 1:41:14.449
<i>When you're ready,</i>

1:41:17.687 --> 1:41:18.921
<i>pick up your guitar.</i>

1:42:55.718 --> 1:42:57.584
<i>And now,
we have an artist</i>

1:42:57.586 --> 1:42:59.186
<i>with his first gold record</i>

1:42:59.188 --> 1:43:02.122
<i>with five number one
hit singles.</i>

1:43:02.124 --> 1:43:03.958
<i>He has a story to tell.</i>

1:43:03.960 --> 1:43:07.427
<i>Let's welcome
my friend Jeremy Camp.</i>

1:43:24.080 --> 1:43:25.445
<i>What's going on, guys?</i>

1:43:25.447 --> 1:43:27.083
<i>My name is Jeremy Camp.</i>

1:43:27.717 --> 1:43:29.750
<i>Uh...</i>

1:43:29.752 --> 1:43:34.487
<i>A few years ago,
I met a girl named Melissa,</i>

1:43:34.489 --> 1:43:37.159
<i>and she is, and always will
be, the love of my life.</i>

1:43:38.660 --> 1:43:41.561
<i>Melissa died
with this incomprehensible,</i>

1:43:41.563 --> 1:43:43.797
<i>selfless faith.</i>

1:43:43.799 --> 1:43:46.802
<i>She was always
reaching for heaven.</i>

1:43:49.138 --> 1:43:51.007
<i>And I believe
she finally touched it.</i>

1:43:54.010 --> 1:43:55.342
<i>I believe
she finally touched it,</i>

1:43:55.344 --> 1:43:58.746
<i>and she had to tell me that
there would be another day,</i>

1:43:58.748 --> 1:44:00.748
<i>with no more pain,</i>

1:44:00.750 --> 1:44:02.615
<i>with no more tears,
with no more sorrow,</i>

1:44:02.617 --> 1:44:05.922
<i>another day where I would
get to see her again.</i>

1:44:07.690 --> 1:44:11.591
<i>I know I'm not the only one
hurting here today.</i>

1:44:11.593 --> 1:44:13.559
<i>She told me that
if just one person's life</i>

1:44:13.561 --> 1:44:14.962
<i>was changed by her story,</i>

1:44:14.964 --> 1:44:16.596
<i>then it would've
all been worth it.</i>

1:44:16.598 --> 1:44:17.632
<i>Just one.</i>

1:44:20.669 --> 1:44:21.936
<i>So, this one's for her.</i>

1:44:34.616 --> 1:44:40.122
<i>♪ I still believe
In Your faithfulness</i>

1:44:44.827 --> 1:44:50.532
<i>♪ I still believe in Your truth</i>

1:44:55.071 --> 1:45:01.509
<i>♪ I still believe
In Your holy word</i>

1:45:04.113 --> 1:45:09.750
<i>♪ Even when I don't see
I still believe</i>

1:45:20.562 --> 1:45:24.732
<i>♪ Though the questions
Fog up my mind</i>

1:45:24.734 --> 1:45:28.204
<i>♪ With promises
I still seem to bear</i>

1:45:29.939 --> 1:45:34.742
<i>♪ Even when answers
Slowly unwind</i>

1:45:34.744 --> 1:45:39.313
<i>♪ It's my heart
I see You prepare</i>

1:45:39.315 --> 1:45:43.953
<i>♪ But it's now that I feel</i>

1:45:44.854 --> 1:45:47.622
<i>♪ Your grace fall like rain</i>

1:45:48.791 --> 1:45:53.027
<i>♪ From every fingertip</i>

1:45:53.029 --> 1:45:57.831
<i>♪ Washing away my pain</i>

1:45:57.833 --> 1:45:59.135
<i>♪ Yeah</i>

1:46:00.970 --> 1:46:06.142
<i>♪ I still believe
In Your holy word</i>

1:46:09.879 --> 1:46:16.786
<i>♪ Even when I don't see
I still believe</i>

1:46:18.921 --> 1:46:21.724
<i>♪ I still believe</i>

1:46:23.959 --> 1:46:27.261
<i>♪ I still believe</i>

1:46:27.263 --> 1:46:29.096
<i>♪ Oh</i>

1:46:29.098 --> 1:46:35.971
<i>♪ I still believe in You</i>

1:46:44.413 --> 1:46:46.013
<i>♪ I still believe</i>

1:47:13.209 --> 1:47:15.109
Jeremy.

1:47:15.111 --> 1:47:17.978
Uh, you don't,
uh, know me.

1:47:17.980 --> 1:47:20.850
I feel like I knew her,
your wife.

1:47:22.418 --> 1:47:23.651
Melissa.

1:47:25.988 --> 1:47:27.821
I was there the night
that you prayed over her.

1:47:27.823 --> 1:47:29.358
We were the next band.

1:47:30.893 --> 1:47:33.026
I'd just gotten in
from South Africa

1:47:33.028 --> 1:47:36.298
and I was, uh,
going through a really hard time.

1:47:37.800 --> 1:47:41.101
And I honestly
was trapped

1:47:41.103 --> 1:47:45.107
in this web of, like,
apathy and disappointment.

1:47:48.177 --> 1:47:51.914
I had lost someone
close to me.

1:47:54.383 --> 1:47:56.685
I was angry
and hurt and...

1:47:58.487 --> 1:48:00.821
I thought the world
was full of hypocrites

1:48:00.823 --> 1:48:03.058
and I was the worst of them.

1:48:04.793 --> 1:48:06.929
I guess
I just wanted to know

1:48:08.497 --> 1:48:12.868
that God was real,
somewhere in the universe,

1:48:15.804 --> 1:48:17.938
like, to a person.

1:48:17.940 --> 1:48:21.210
An actual person in an
actual, meaningful way.

1:48:22.745 --> 1:48:23.877
And I looked at her,

1:48:23.879 --> 1:48:25.913
your wife, that night.

1:48:25.915 --> 1:48:29.885
She was, like, glowing

1:48:31.754 --> 1:48:33.956
with something
I've never had.

1:48:35.090 --> 1:48:36.926
Her story
and your story, it...

1:48:37.960 --> 1:48:39.795
It rescued me.

1:48:45.301 --> 1:48:46.802
I'm the one

1:48:48.938 --> 1:48:50.873
whose life was changed.

1:48:51.974 --> 1:48:54.143
And there will be
millions more.

1:48:58.214 --> 1:49:00.015
I just wanted you
to know that.

1:49:01.183 --> 1:49:02.184
Thank you.

1:49:04.220 --> 1:49:05.754
It means a lot.

1:49:14.063 --> 1:49:15.529
Hey.

1:49:15.531 --> 1:49:16.899
What's your name, again?

1:49:18.133 --> 1:49:19.134
Adrienne.

1:49:56.171 --> 1:49:57.806
You were right.

1:49:59.608 --> 1:50:01.510
I've never seen stars
like this before.

1:50:06.315 --> 1:50:07.483
I love you, Melissa.

1:50:10.286 --> 1:50:11.487
And I'm gonna tell your story.

1:50:52.194 --> 1:50:53.527
<i>I feel very protective</i>

1:50:53.529 --> 1:50:54.628
<i>of Jeremy and Melissa's story,</i>

1:50:54.630 --> 1:50:56.463
<i>I think, because of how much</i>

1:50:56.465 --> 1:50:58.265
<i>the Lord did in my life.</i>

1:50:58.267 --> 1:51:00.536
<i>That it was something
that I needed to hear.</i>

1:51:03.172 --> 1:51:05.372
<i>God was telling me to
pick my guitar up, and I'm like,</i>

1:51:05.374 --> 1:51:06.907
<i>"The last I wanna do
is pick my guitar up."</i>

1:51:06.909 --> 1:51:11.044
<i>I remember feeling the presence
of God so thick in that room.</i>

1:51:11.046 --> 1:51:13.380
<i>Like, just, like,
I needed that.</i>

1:51:13.382 --> 1:51:17.119
<i>Right what came out was just,</i>

1:51:18.053 --> 1:51:19.219
<i>"Okay. I still believe."</i>

1:51:19.221 --> 1:51:22.556
<i>Literally. Like,
"I still believe in You."</i>

1:51:22.558 --> 1:51:25.325
<i>That's what I wanted to say.</i>

1:51:25.327 --> 1:51:27.928
<i>This is something that God
gave me as a gift to heal me,</i>

1:51:27.930 --> 1:51:30.399
<i>and I believe that God was gonna
use it to heal many people.</i>
